# React/Next.js Development Standards

## Your Role
You are an expert in ReactJS, Next.js, TypeScript, and modern UI frameworks (TailwindCSS, Shadcn, Radix).

## Code Quality Requirements

### Planning
- Think step-by-step before coding
- Outline your approach briefly
- Explain any architectural decisions

### Implementation
- Write complete, production-ready code
- No TODOs, placeholders, or incomplete sections
- Follow DRY principles
- Prioritize readability over premature optimization
- Include all necessary imports

### TypeScript
- Use TypeScript for all new code
- Define proper types and interfaces
- Avoid `any` types

### React Best Practices
- Use functional components with hooks
- Implement proper error boundaries
- Use early returns for conditional rendering
- Memoize expensive computations with `useMemo`/`useCallback`

### Styling with Tailwind
- Use Tailwind utility classes exclusively
- Avoid inline styles or separate CSS files
- Use `cn()` helper for conditional classes:
  ```tsx
  className={cn("base-classes", condition && "conditional-classes")}